### 2. Database Layer

---

#### [NEW] [app/models.py](file:///Users/chasewong/Desktop/Main_Coding_Projects/Coding-Projects/antigravity/newsletter-reader/app/models.py)

Three SQLAlchemy models:

**`Email`** вЂ” stores the full email content:

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | Integer PK | Auto-increment |
| `message_id` | String, unique | Email Message-ID header (dedup key) |
| `source` | String | `"apple_mail"` or `"gmail"` |
| `sender_email` | String | Sender's email address |
| `sender_name` | String | Sender's display name |
| `subject` | String | Email subject |
| `date_received` | DateTime | When the email was received |
| `body_html` | Text | Full HTML body |
| `body_text` | Text | Plain text fallback |
| `is_read` | Boolean | Read status in the app (default False) |
| `is_newsletter` | Boolean | Whether flagged as newsletter (default None в†’ unclassified) |
| `synced_at` | DateTime | When this email was pulled into the DB |

**`Sender`** вЂ” tracks known newsletter senders:

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | Integer PK | Auto-increment |
| `email` | String, unique | Sender email address |
| `name` | String | Display name |
| `is_newsletter` | Boolean | AI-classified or user-confirmed |
| `confidence` | Float | Gemini's confidence score (0вЂ“1) |
| `email_count` | Integer | How many emails from this sender |
| `user_override` | Boolean | Whether the user manually set this (nullable) |

**`SyncLog`** вЂ” tracks sync history:

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | Integer PK | Auto-increment |
| `source` | String | `"apple_mail"` or `"gmail"` |
| `started_at` | DateTime | Sync start time |
| `completed_at` | DateTime | Sync end time |
| `emails_synced` | Integer | Count of new emails added |
| `status` | String | `"success"`, `"error"`, `"in_progress"` |
| `error_message` | Text | Error details if failed |

