### 3. Email Source Services

---

#### [NEW] [app/services/apple\_mail.py](file:///Users/chasewong/Desktop/Main_Coding_Projects/Coding-Projects/antigravity/newsletter-reader/app/services/apple_mail.py)

Apple Mail reader using `subprocess` + `osascript`:

- **`is_available()`** вЂ” checks if running on macOS and Mail.app is accessible
- **`fetch_emails(limit=500)`** вЂ” executes AppleScript to retrieve emails:
  - Uses `tell application "Mail"` to iterate inbox messages
  - Retrieves: `message id`, `sender`, `subject`, `date received`, `source` (raw MIME content for HTML extraction)
  - Returns list of dicts
- **`_parse_mime_source(raw_source)`** вЂ” uses Python's `email` library to extract HTML body from raw MIME content
- **AppleScript strategy**: Fetch emails in batches (e.g., 50 at a time) to avoid AppleScript timeout issues. Use the `source` property for HTML extraction since `content` only returns plain text.

> [!NOTE]
> AppleScript interaction with Mail.app is inherently slow (~0.5вЂ“1s per message for `source`). For large inboxes, the initial sync may take several minutes. The UI will show progress.

---

#### [NEW] [app/services/gmail.py](file:///Users/chasewong/Desktop/Main_Coding_Projects/Coding-Projects/antigravity/newsletter-reader/app/services/gmail.py)

Gmail API client:

- **`is_configured()`** вЂ” checks if `credentials.json` exists
- **`authenticate()`** вЂ” handles OAuth2 flow:
  - Uses `InstalledAppFlow` for initial auth (opens browser)
  - Stores token in `credentials/token.json`
  - Auto-refreshes expired tokens
  - Scope: `gmail.readonly`
- **`fetch_emails(limit=500)`** вЂ” retrieves emails:
  - `messages().list()` to get message IDs
  - `messages().get(format='full')` for each message
  - Recursively parses MIME parts to extract `text/html` and `text/plain`
  - Base64url-decodes body content
  - Extracts headers: `From`, `Subject`, `Date`, `Message-ID`
  - Returns list of dicts matching the same format as `apple_mail.py`
- **Rate limiting** вЂ” respects Gmail API quotas with exponential backoff

---

#### [NEW] [app/services/sync\_engine.py](file:///Users/chasewong/Desktop/Main_Coding_Projects/Coding-Projects/antigravity/newsletter-reader/app/services/sync_engine.py)

Orchestrates syncing from both sources:

- **`sync_all()`** вЂ” runs Apple Mail + Gmail sync sequentially
- **`sync_source(source_name)`** вЂ” syncs a specific source
- **Deduplication** вЂ” uses `message_id` (Message-ID header) to skip already-synced emails
- **Incremental sync** вЂ” on subsequent syncs, only fetch emails newer than the last sync timestamp
- **Progress tracking** вЂ” updates `SyncLog` entries in real-time
- **Error handling** вЂ” catches per-source errors so one failing doesn't block the other
- **Post-sync hook** вЂ” after sync, trigger newsletter detection for any unclassified senders

